<br>
Firstly, said evil gnome proffered the following 'story'..<br>
<br>
'I remember Fimble's first date. He brought her over for a little visit before they were to head out together. I was a little shocked when I first met her, because I thought my son could do better. Her name was Mupple and she was about as pretty as her name. She was missing one of her front teeth while the others didn't quite know which way to grow. She had sandy hair, but it had spots of black in it here and there. She had a big, round face that jiggled when she talked with that annoying lisp she had. She looked almost as bad as the tart my husband brought home that one time... Oh, never mind! She was a horrid little creature that I'll never forget!<br>
<br>
When I first met her I could hardly believe she was a Gnome, but I greeted her as pleasantly as a mother should. I didn't say too much about her appearance or her manners because I try to be a tolerant mother. She wouldn't warm up to me and wouldn't let me get close enough to sniff her. As all good mothers know, you can tell a lot about your son's dates with a good sniff! So I tried to calm her down by offering a little Gnomish Spirits. She kept refusing, saying she was too young to drink. Imagine! Poor child, what her parents must have put her through! So I explained to her that in the Piddlebitz household all babies are fed beer instead of milk because the women have problems with... Oh, never mind! She gives dear Fimble a funny look and asks me if that could harm the children, but I set her straight and tell her to just look at what a fine specimen of manhood Fimble turned out to be! She gives him another of those funny looks and that's when I start to dislike her.<br>
<br>
What's a mother to do? Well, the Piddlebitzs are well known for our honesty and forthrightness, so I told her exactly what I thought of her. She screamed and cried at me and told Fimble what a horrible mother I was. Poor child, she just didn't have a proper upbringing! That's when Fimble perked up and said, &quot;Well now that ya got that off yer chest, let's head out, Babe.&quot; Oh, he's such an adorable little chap! Too good for that wench! But the wicked wretch slapped him and ran out.<br>
<br>
Fimble never brought another girl over after that. I guess he decided to become a loner. *Sigh* I keep praying to Brell that he'll settle down one day.' <br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, it's longwinded, but that's to bore you into not reading his lies. Next, the true story as told by his victim.<br>
<br>
<br>
'Passing through Innothule the other day, I comely Troll warrior handed me a screwed up bit of parchment. Although heavily stained with who knows what, I could make out some kind of scrawl on it. The troll informed me that he had been accosted by two gnomes and wanted the 'werld to no abowt it'. So here it is, transcribed directly from the crumpled troll epistle:<br>
<br>
Deer evrybodie, I am a trollie of fyoo werds but I gota tel yoo a warnin story abowt a nommie I met in da swamp de uver day. Dis litul chap runs up to me an starts yakkin at me. Sumfink abowt makin sum shoos for my prity feets... Enyway, he interjoosed himself as Fimble an asked wot my prity litul name mite be. Hur hur, dis litul chap wos reel drunk I hafta tel yoo an altho I am indeed a seks masheen, I neva bin cald prity or litul befor. I told him my name wos Madbastad an he askd if he cud jus cal me Maddie. I sed as long as he gav me da grog he cud cal me Sherly.<br>
<br>
He tuk me on a long trip, but I got grog an snaks, so it wos al gud. He tuk me to see his momma. Ooh boy she is ugleee!! Nevrdaless she wos kind an gav me som mor grog as I wos upset by her ugleeness and she smelt of weewee. Made a poor trollie pine for his home  <br>
<br>
Dis wumman yabberd as much as her sun, mebbe mor abowt shoos, mebbe not. Enyway, Fimble, who had bin playin wiv some dollies owtside or sumfink came bak in and sed we shud go 'behind da winmils'. I askd wot he ment and he wisperd sumfink I cud not eva repeet, evun to my momma! So I gav him a gud bash on top of his shinee hed and legd it reel kwik bak to da swamp.<br>
<br>
I dont no if I wil ever see dat litul nommie agen, but nekst time, I anser no kweschuns - I just eet da litul buger.<br>
<br>
-- So there you have it. Fimble's first date as it really was. Not that I'm surprised.. '<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Shockingly, not many people became wise to his ways and I have just noticed this on his very pages. I thought it wise to spread the warning...<br>
<br>
<br>
'Helo al yoo peepul hoo kum to dis playce to get noo shoos. I hav bin havin ferupee for mi preevyus encownta wiv Fimble an if yoo can remembuh wot hapund, he tryde to sijooce me. Mi emoshunul scars hav heeld now, but I hav to worn yoo dat he is stil prayin on da inussent amung yoo.<br>
<br>
I hav herd froo da graypvine dat he is selin his shooz - not fur munnie, but for payment in kynde! Da convasashun wud go sumfing like dis:<br>
<br>
Fimble da evul nommie: Hey chickie baby - how abowt I mayk yoo sum shooz?<br>
<br>
Inucent femayl elf: Wot kynd of shooz, you creepy litul dood?<br>
<br>
Fimble da now slobbering evul nommie: Luvly slipers for yor luvly feets, mi anjul. (this is wen he liks his lips and slivers up clos...)<br>
<br>
Inucent femayl elf: hm, wel ok - how mush do dey cost?<br>
<br>
Fimble da evul nommie wiv a bulj in his rowb: for yoo huny, just rub dis clokwerk devise in mi pokit and we cal it kwits, ok?<br>
<br>
Femayl elf is den jooped into tuchin evul Fimble on his sokit set.<br>
<br>
Yoo hav bin warnd!<br>
<br>
Lots of luv, Madbastad. Rongd luver and prowd trollie killa.' <br>
